text.tspan: Human Development Index vs. Mean male height, 1996
The Human Development Index (HDI) is a summary measure of key dimensions of human development: a long
and healthy life, being knowledgeable and having a decent standard of living. It's measured from 0 to 1 (where
higher is better). This is shown against mean male height in adults by year of birth
Mean male height by year of birth
Source: United Nations Development Programme, Human Development Report 2020, NCD RisC, Human Height (2017)
